HEADWORD: Thiophene
<hw>Thi"o*phene</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Thio-</ets>
+ <ets>ph</ets>enyl + <ets>-ene</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>A
sulphur hydrocarbon, <chform>C4H4S</chform>, analogous to furfuran and
benzene, and acting as the base of a large number of substances which
closely resemble the corresponding aromatic derivatives.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

